	<div id="event_content_container">
			<ul class="head_ul">
				<li class="head_ul_li">	
					<div id="content_ardeur12" class="event_contents">
						<br><span style="font-size:25px; font-weight:900;">ARDEUR 2012</span><br>
						Ardeur 2012, the first step taken by the IT Association in order to achieve its motto - Together with a vision towards transformation - was organized on the 3rd of October, 2012. Ardeur, a French word meaning passion, was a set of successful competitions that successfully managed to induce much enthusiasm amongst the students.<br>
						It was divided into three sub-events :<br>
						 <br><span style="font-size:20px;">Minute to win it</span><br>
						This event consisted of a set of very enthusing tasks that had to be executed within sixty seconds and the team with the best time was awarded with useful goodies. A team of two was formed for the activities. Activities included questions on identifying promotional clips of latest technologies as well as tasks like rolling eggs for a certain distance! The event was also witnessed by the Vice President of the Association- Mrs. Nimala K.<br>
						<br><span style="font-size:20px;">Strain your brain</span><br>
						The format of this event was like that of a quiz with several rounds; the questionnaire containing questions from both technical and non-technical domains. The event comprised of three rounds. A team consisting of two members was a pre requisite for the event. The quiz was written, visual and audio in nature i.e the questions were also based on various audio video clips and blurred images and similar challenging questions. The top two winning teams were awarded with useful goodies by the event coordinators.<br>
						<br><span style="font-size:20px;">Gaming event</span><br>
						It consisted of two games, NFS (Need for Speed) Most wanted and CS(Counter strike). NFS was a one on one competition and the tournament was knock out in nature while CS was a team event. Two teams were made to battle against each other till one laid still on ground. The participation number was recorded to be forty-three teams.<br>
					</div>
				</li>
				<li class="head_ul_li">
					<div id="content_furor13" class="event_contents">	
						<br><span style="font-size:25px; font-weight:900;">FUROR 2013</span><br>
						Furor '13, 15th and 16th February, 2013 will always be remembered as IT Association's huge success. As it was a technical event, it was quite challenging. The IT Association worked really hard to organize all the events. A total of five exciting events took place namely: Treasure Hunt, Placement Buzz, Tech a thon, Paper Presentation and Gaming (CS and DOTA). It was a team event and the rules for taking part were quite easy. Each team was supposed to have two members only except for gaming in which each team consisted of five members. One of the most interesting events was Treasure Hunt which required technical knowledge about coding and decoding and the questions were asked based on the programming languages like C, C++ and JAVA. Separate question sets were prepared for each team. The other appealing event was Placement Buzz which was meant for 2nd and 3rd year students. It involved dealing with interview scenario. It had three levels which weren't easy to cross. They were Aptitude and Verbal, Technical knowledge and Personal Interview. The event was quite a successful one.<br><br>
						<br><span style="font-size:20px;">Paper Presentation</span><br>
						Paper Presentation was another event that took place. It was meant for students of all years. They were supposed to send the extract of their presentation at clubteamit@gmail.com. The topics for the paper presentation were: Cyber crime and Forensics Cloud computing 4G technology Green computing Sixth sense technology Digital jewellery Body networks sensors<br><br>
						<br><span style="font-size:20px;">Tech-A-Thon</span><br>
						Tech a thon, an attractive event, basically dealt with web pages and company logos. It too consisted of two levels. The first level was based on awareness and it required the participants to guess the logos which were shown to them in a puzzled manner. The next level involved replication of the shown web page in paint.<br>
						<br><span style="font-size:20px;">Gaming event</span><br>
						The most exciting event and the event which grabbed the attention of all gaming freaks was Gaming. This event got maximum registrations and gave a platform to all the game lovers to show their gaming talent. There were two games CS and DOTA. CS involved four rounds. As it was a knock out event the losing teams were eliminated. First two rounds were race to 11 rounds and last two rounds were race to 15 round. Total 13 teams participated in CS. The other game was DOTA. It was also a knock out event. It involved three rounds and total six teams participated in it. The winners of each event were awarded prizes and were honored. This event was a great success and provided an exposure to both the participants and the organizers. Hopefully, the association will plan and will include many more appealing events in near future.<br><br>
					</div>
				</li>
				<li class="head_ul_li">	<div id="content_ardeur13" class="event_contents">
							<br><span style="font-size:25px; font-weight:900;">ARDEUR 2013</span><br>
							<br><span style="font-size:23px;">THE EXORDIUM</span><br>
							The commencement of the amazing event Ardeur was done by Mr. Rajendran , our esteemed HOD, and several other department teachers . The chief idea behind the inauguration was to gangplank the gap between the teachers and the students. This ceremony gave the teachers an opportunity to brush up their memory and have some fun. The idea behind keeping this ceremony was very pensive. The teachers were made to play some games to become informal and make merry. They were made to play two games. First one constituted of picking up chits and performing the informal and easy tasks written in them. Everyone was astonished by the huge amount of talent showcased by our endeared faculty. Second game consisted of turning the hands of time and taking the faculty to their childhood days and making them play lemon and spoon race. The winners of the prodigious game were Mrs. Kayal and Mrs. Safa. This was a kick start to Ardeur’13 and was conducted with lots of enthusiasm and entertainment.<br>
							<br><span style="font-size:23px;">BEFORE THE SHOWDOWN</span><br>
							They say that “the difference between ordinary and extra ordinary is that little extra” and every member of the IT Association has contributed to that “extra” and made Ardeur’13 impeccable. The event had a record of 500+ common registrations for various events which comprised of-<br><br>
							<ul>
								<li>Inaugral Event &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<sub>(exclusive for faculty)</sub></li>
								<li>Oratio</li>
								<li>Braincastic</li>
								<li>Innovace</li>
								<li>Constrain</li>
								<li>Gaming</li>
							</ul>

							<br><br><span style="font-size:23px;">Braincastic (The know it all quiz)</span><br>
							<br>Braincastic was a team based non technical event. Each team was required to have 2 members. On the whole there were 256 participants. Organized by Dhiraj Kumar and Chirag Mehta with the help of four volunteers, the event executed successfully. The first two rounds were conducted on 13th and the final rounds on 14th September.<br>
							<br><ul>
									<li><span style="font-size:22px;">Round 1: The Jujubi Questionnaire</span><br><ul>In this round the participants were given two sets of question papers which had 50 questions each and they had 20 minutes to solve it. The questions covered encyclopedic topics. Out of 128 teams 35 were short listed for the next round which raised the arduousness bar.</ul></li><br>
									<li><span style="font-size:22px;">Round 2: Rapid Fire</span><br><ul>The 35 selected teams had a rapid fire for duration of 1 minute where they were asked 20 questions. The questions were general and an endeavor to test their quick response.</ul></li><br>
									<li><span style="font-size:22px;">Round 3: Audio Visual</span><br><ul>The top 10 teams were taken and tested on how well they keep themselves updated and so, the topics like sports, advertisements, etc were included. Top 5 teams were filtered that made it to the final round.</ul></li><br>
									<li><span style="font-size:22px;">Round 4: The Mega Quiz Shadow run</span><br><ul>The quiz had to be answered from 6 spectacular categories. The top scorers were given higher priority to choose from:<br><br>&nbsp;SportsBasic, Science, Incredible, Current Affairs, Entertainment, Mythology<br><br>The top two teams were awarded the first two positions with the prize money of Rs 1700 and Rs 800 respectively.</ul></li><br>
								</ul>
							<br><span style="font-size:23px;">Constrain (Con me if you can)</span><br>
							<br>Dhiraj Kumar and Chirag Mehta organized the event assisted by 4 volunteers. Ithe event was conducted on 13 and 14th September in Tech Park room no. 403. It was an individual event. The first two rounds took place on 13th Sept from 1.30 to 4.00pm and the other two rounds on 14th September from 9.00am- 1.00 pm.<br>
							<br><ul>
									<li><span style="font-size:22px;">Round 1: Signature for grey decode</span><br><ul>The participants were given the signatures of three famous personalities to forge. Six sets of question papers were provided with three signatures. The decoder had colored commas between the personalities which had to be realized by the participant for further rounds. 15 minutes were allotted.</ul></li><br>
									<li><span style="font-size:22px;">Round 2: Game-O-Holic</span><br><ul>This was accompanied by round 1 on the same day which had 30 participants. The participants were divided into two slots. There were two sub rounds for the participants. One was Minesweeper and the other was Pocket tabs.<br>The 15 winners of minesweeper became players in Pocket Tanks.</ul></li><br>
									<li><span style="font-size:22px;">Round 3: Mr. Cube</span><br><ul>30 participants were qualified. The task was to sort the color they found in round 1. 10 participants completed the task successfully and moved to the final round.</ul></li><br>
									<li><span style="font-size:22px;">Round 4:</span><br><ul>It had three sub-rounds. Phase 1 was fastest finger, where they had to quickly write a jocular story. Phase 2 was error mirror, where the participants had to type an erroneous passage exactly as it is without any correction. The last phase was called Jumbled Keys, where 5 paragraphs were to be typed using a mapped keyboard.</ul></li><br>
								</ul>
							<br><span style="font-size:23px;">Innovace</span><br>
							<br>This was the only technical event organized by Palash Garg, assisted by two other volunteers. It consisted of three rounds. The event was conducted on 13 and 14th September.<br>
							<br><ul>
									<li><span style="font-size:22px;">Round 1: Gadgets and Gizmo</span><br><ul>The participants were shown distorted and blurred images of gadgets and latest devices. Those who identified them correctly earned a point.</ul></li><br>
									<li><span style="font-size:22px;">Round 2: The Mighty Quiz</span><br><ul>Each participant was to answer a set of 4 questions. They were filtered according to the correctness of the answer into the next round.</ul></li><br>
									<li><span style="font-size:22px;">Round 3: Go Gooled!</span><br><ul>This was an exciting round where the participants were provided with Google Search engine for searching answers to 25 questions provided to them. The twist in this round was that a time limit was given to the participants and as one question was answered, the time was reduced for the other.  Shashank Bharadwaj emerged as the tech star.<br>The event attracted 200+ participants.</ul></li><br>
								</ul>
							<br><span style="font-size:23px;">ORATIO</span><br>
							<br>This event was specifically for those who love speaking and was held in Tech Park on 13th and 14th September. The event was organized by Richa Bala with the help of Rajini Piya and 7 other volunteers. In this event not only the content but also the confidence and presentation of the participant was taken into consideration for evaluation. There were 3 rounds, from which the first round was held on 13th and the 2nd and the 3rd rounds were held on 14th September.<br>
							<br><ul>
									<li><span style="font-size:23px;">ROUND 1:  Group Discussion</span><br><ul>In this round, the participants were given a topic which has choices, whatever they wish to they are free to opt and accordingly they have to support their argument. There were about 61 participants and the round was conducted in 3 slots, where in each slot 20 could participate. The topics were general in nature and comprehended social and technical topics. From each slot 8 participants were selected for the next round.</ul></li>
									<li><span style="font-size:23px;">ROUND 2:  Extempore</span><br><ul>This round,  as the name suggests, is all about how well you can present the topic for the given time. The 24 shortlisted participants got to pick up their topic randomly. The topics included proverbs and general topics. The whole round was carried out in single session and the best 10 participants were chosen from the lot for the final round. </ul></li>
									<li><span style="font-size:23px;">ROUND 3: Debate</span><br><ul>	The final round was the debate, which was one on one for the 10 finalists. They were divided into 5 teams and each team was given a topic and for which one of them had to support the given issue and there by other had to contradict it. The process of selection of team and topic was done based on the chits. After a rigorous battle of words there were two winners, and a best speaker who was not only confident but also had presented oneself the best was chosen.</ul></li>
								</ul>
							<br><br>
						</div>
				</li>
